2009年至2013年間，布林肯擔任總統奧巴馬的副助理和副總統拜登的國家安全顧問。在職期間，他協助政府制定美國對[[阿富汗|阿富汗]]、[[巴基斯坦|巴基斯坦]]及[[伊朗|伊朗]]核計劃的政策。<ref name=Columbia14>{{cite web|url=https://www.law.columbia.edu/news/archive/senate-confirms-antony-tony-blinken-88-deputy-secretary-state|title=Senate Confirms Antony "Tony" Blinken '88 as Secretary of State|date=2014-12-17|publisher=[[哥倫比亞法學院|哥倫比亞法學院]]|access-date=2020-11-26|archive-date=2020-09-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919002343/https://www.law.columbia.edu/news/archive/senate-confirms-antony-tony-blinken-88-deputy-secretary-state|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=Sanger>{{cite news |title=Obama Makes His Choice for No. 2 Post at State Department |last=Sanger |first=David E. |author-link=David E. Sanger |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/08/world/middleeast/antony-blinken-is-obamas-choice-for-no-2-state-department-post.html |work=[[紐約時報|紐約時報]] |date=07-11-2014 |access-date=03-02-2015 |archive-date=2015-02-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150220023847/http://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/08/world/middleeast/antony-blinken-is-obamas-choice-for-no-2-state-department-post.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>在奧巴馬於[[2012年美國總統選舉|2012年總統選舉]]取得連任後，布林肯於第二任政府任期開始時轉任國家安全副顧問一職。<ref>{{cite news |title=Biden confidant Antony Blinken expected to get key foreign policy role |author=Michael Martina, Simon Lewis, Arshad Mohammed |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-election-biden-blinken-newsmaker/biden-confidant-antony-blinken-expected-to-get-key-foreign-policy-role-idUSKBN27R1B |publisher=[[路透社|路透社]] |date=2020-11-11 |access-date=2021-01-20 }}{{Dead link}}</ref>2014年11月，奧巴馬提名布林肯擔任副國務卿，接替離職的[[威廉·約瑟夫·伯恩斯|威廉·約瑟夫·伯恩斯]]。<ref>{{cite news|title=Obama nominates his adviser Tony Blinken as Deputy Secretary of State|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-politics-blinken-idUSKBN0IR2F320141107|access-date=07-11-2014|publisher=[[路透社|路透社]]|archive-date=2016-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126064513/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-politics-blinken-idUSKBN0IR2F320141107|dead-url=no}}</ref>翌月，[[美國參議院|參議院]]以55票對38票的投票結果確認布林肯的提名。<ref>{{Cite web|title=U.S. Senate: U.S. Senate Roll Call Votes 113th Congress - 2nd Session|url=https://www.senate.gov/legislative/LIS/roll_call_lists/roll_call_vote_cfm.cfm?congress=113&session=2&vote=00362|access-date=08-01-2019|website=senate.gov|archive-date=2018-09-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180925083221/https://www.senate.gov/legislative/LIS/roll_call_lists/roll_call_vote_cfm.cfm?congress=113&session=2&vote=00362|dead-url=no}}</ref>

奧巴馬在2011年決定[[奧薩瑪·賓·拉登之死|殺死奧薩瑪·賓·拉登]]時，布林肯評論「我從未見過領導人作出比這更勇敢的決定」。<ref>{{Cite book|last1=Mann|first1=Jim|url=https://archive.org/details/obamiansstruggle0000mann/page/313/mode/1up|title=The Obamians: The Struggle Inside the White House to Redefine American Power|date=2012|publisher=[[維京出版社|維京出版社]]|isbn=9780670023769|location=紐約|pages=313|language=en|oclc=1150993166}}</ref>2013年，美國政府的個人履歷描述布林肯為「政府在起草[[敘利亞|敘利亞]]政策中的重要人物之一」，<ref name="twp"/>而布林肯則擔任向公眾解釋對敘利亞政策的工作。<ref name="starturn">{{Cite news|last1=Allen|first1=Jonathan|date=2013-09-16|title=Tony Blinken's star turn|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2013/09/tony-blinkens-star-turn-096847|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200828173731/https://www.politico.com/story/2013/09/tony-blinkens-star-turn-096847|archive-date=2020-08-28|access-date=2020-11-23|work=[[Politico|Politico]]|language=en|dead-url=no}}</ref>布林肯支持2011年[[2011年多國武裝干涉利比亞|對利比亞的軍事干預]]，<ref name="starturn" />以及對[[叙利亚反对派|叙利亚反对派]]提供武器援助。<ref>{{cite news |title=W.H. defends plan to arm Syrian rebels |url=https://edition.cnn.com/videos/bestoftv/2014/09/18/house-approves-aid-to-syrian-rebels-blinken-interview-newday.cnn |publisher=CNN |date=2014-09-18 |access-date=2020-11-23 |archive-date=2017-10-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171019115424/http://edition.cnn.com/videos/bestoftv/2014/09/18/house-approves-aid-to-syrian-rebels-blinken-interview-newday.cnn |dead-url=no }}</ref>在[[2014年烏克蘭革命|2014年烏克蘭革命]]之後，布林肯亦影響了奧巴馬政府對[[俄羅斯兼併克里米亞|俄羅斯兼併克里米亞]]的回應。<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Gramer|first1=Robbie|last2=Detsch|first2=Jack|title=Biden's Secretary of State Pick Bodes Return to Normalcy for Weary Diplomats|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/11/23/biden-blinken-transition-state-department/|access-date=2020-11-25|website=[[外交政策_(雜誌)|外交政策]]|language=en-US|date=2020-11-23|archive-date=2020-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125055809/https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/11/23/biden-blinken-transition-state-department/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last1=Zeleny|first1=Jeff|last2=Merica|first2=Dan|last3=Atwood|first3=Kylie|title=Biden poised to nominate Antony Blinken as secretary of state|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/11/22/politics/biden-transition-antony-blinken/index.html|access-date=2020-11-25|website=[[有線電視新聞網|CNN]]|date=2020-11-22|archive-date=2020-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125143545/https://www.cnn.com/2020/11/22/politics/biden-transition-antony-blinken/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>同年，在[[2014年以巴衝突|2014年以巴衝突]]期間，布林肯與拜登合作，要求美國提供資金補充以色列[[鐵穹防禦系統|鐵穹防禦系統]]的[[反彈道飛彈|反彈道飛彈]]。<ref name="timesofisrael">{{cite news|last=Magid|first=Jacob|title=In tapping Blinken, Biden will be served by confidant with deep Jewish roots|url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/in-tapping-blinken-biden-will-be-served-by-confidante-with-deep-jewish-roots/|work=[[以色列時報|以色列時報]]|date=2020-11-24|access-date=03-12-2020|archive-date=2020-11-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130103504/https://www.timesofisrael.com/in-tapping-blinken-biden-will-be-served-by-confidante-with-deep-jewish-roots/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

